A particle is moving in a circular path of radius $r$ at a constant speed $v$. Which one of the following graphs correctly represents its acceleration $a$?

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{cc}
\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[axis lines=left,xlabel={$r$},ylabel={$a$},xtick=\empty,ytick=\empty,xmin=0,xmax=4,ymin=0,ymax=3,width=5cm,height=4cm]\addplot[black,thick] coordinates {(0,2) (4,2)};\end{axis}\end{tikzpicture} &
\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[axis lines=left,xlabel={$r$},ylabel={$a$},xtick=\empty,ytick=\empty,xmin=0,xmax=4,ymin=0,ymax=4,width=5cm,height=4cm]\addplot[black,thick] {0.5+0.8*x};\end{axis}\end{tikzpicture}\\[4mm]
\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[axis lines=left,xlabel={$r$},ylabel={$a$},xtick=\empty,ytick=\empty,xmin=0,xmax=3,ymin=0,ymax=4,width=5cm,height=4cm,domain=0:2.5]\addplot[black,thick] {0.5*x^2};\end{axis}\end{tikzpicture} &
\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[axis lines=left,xlabel={$r$},ylabel={$a$},xtick=\empty,ytick=\empty,xmin=0,xmax=5,ymin=0,ymax=5,width=5cm,height=4cm,domain=0.5:4.5]\addplot[black,thick] {4/x};\end{axis}\end{tikzpicture}
\end{tabular}
\end{center}
